sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as User / kubectl
    participant K8sAPI as K8s API Server<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Webhook as Admission Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Operator as Model Registry Operator<br/>(controller-runtime)
    participant KubeRBAC as kube-rbac-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Registry as Model Registry REST<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Catalog as Model Catalog<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP
    participant Client as API Client
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over User, Operator: Flow 1: Model Registry Instance Deployment
        User->>K8sAPI: Create ModelRegistry CR<br/>Bearer Token / TLS 1.2+
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: Validate & Mutate<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS (cert-manager TLS)
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Defaults applied, validated
        K8sAPI-->>User: CR created
        K8sAPI->>Operator: Watch event (ModelRegistry)
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Deployment<br/>(registry REST + kube-rbac-proxy sidecar)<br/>SA Token / TLS
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Service (8443/TCP)<br/>SA Token / TLS
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create Route (reencrypt TLS)<br/>SA Token / TLS
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create PostgreSQL Deployment + Service<br/>SA Token / TLS
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create RBAC (Role, RoleBinding, Group)<br/>SA Token / TLS
        Operator->>K8sAPI: Create NetworkPolicies<br/>SA Token / TLS
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Client, PostgreSQL: Flow 2: Model Registry REST API Access (kube-rbac-proxy)
        Client->>Route: POST /v1/model_registry/<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, Bearer Token
        Route->>KubeRBAC: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (reencrypt TLS)
        KubeRBAC->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Token<br/>(can user GET services/{name}?)
        K8sAPI-->>KubeRBAC: Allowed / Denied
        KubeRBAC->>Registry: Forward to localhost<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (loopback, no auth)
        Registry->>PostgreSQL: Query metadata<br/>5432/TCP, Password auth<br/>Optional SSL
        PostgreSQL-->>Registry: Results
        Registry-->>KubeRBAC: JSON Response
        KubeRBAC-->>Route: Encrypted response
        Route-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Client, PostgreSQL: Flow 3: Model Catalog Access
        Client->>Route: GET /api/model_catalog/<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, Bearer Token
        Route->>KubeRBAC: Forward request<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS (reencrypt TLS)
        KubeRBAC->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>443/TCP HTTPS, SA Token<br/>(can user GET services/model-catalog?)
        K8sAPI-->>KubeRBAC: Allowed / Denied
        KubeRBAC->>Catalog: Forward to localhost<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (loopback, no auth)
        Catalog->>PostgreSQL: Query catalog data<br/>5432/TCP, Password auth
        PostgreSQL-->>Catalog: Results
        Catalog-->>KubeRBAC: JSON Response
        KubeRBAC-->>Route: Encrypted response
        Route-->>Client: JSON Response
    end
